   <h2>
    Data
    <em>
    </em>
   </h2>
  </header>
  <div class="col-1">
   <div>
    <p>
     UC Berkeley’s Fung Institute, with sponsorships from the Ewing Marion Kauffman Foundation and Silatech, has collected and aggregated data on global crowdfunding platforms with the goal of distributing information to researchers, policy experts and government officials in their efforts to guide policy and academic research.
    </p>
    <p>
     The database currently contains 6 global crowdfunding-platforms and their campaigns between 2005 and 2014. There are 3 different categories of crowdfunding platforms including reward/donation, equity and lending-based models. You can download for models, platforms, campaigns, project goal, amount, duration and backers information.
    </p>
   </div>
   <h1 style="text-align: left;">
   </h1>
  </div>
  <div class="col-2">
   <p>
    <strong>
     Important Notes
    </strong>
   </p>
   <p>
    This query tool provides an interface to direct access our MYSQL database. Please read the schema description in advance and specify some filters as it greatly reduces time taken for the search and size of the resulting file.
   </p>
   <p>
    <strong>
     Get Started
    </strong>
   </p>
   <p>
    Please register or login using the link below.
   </p>
   <p>
    Click on “Download” to make a query and download. The data will be delivered to your registered e-mail address.
   </p>
   <h5 style="text-align: left;">
    <a href="http://rosencrantz.berkeley.edu/crowdfunding/index.php" target="_blank">
     DATABASE
    </a>
   </h5>
  </div>
 </div>
</section>
